<p>
<seg id=1> US President Clinton promised to provide new financial aid on the World AIDS Day in order to prevent this deadly disease, and this includes more research appropriation. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton has planned to increase 30% more funds for AIDS reseach for the National Hygiene Research Institute. </seg>
<seg id=3> He also planned to announce an appropriation of 10 million dollars for taking care of the AIDS children. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton administration also indicated that this increased reseach funds is the biggest one-time investment ever made by the American public funds for AIDS research. </seg>
</p>
